The IPWE calculation

10 folds cross validations. 100 repetitions.

The trajectories

Fit the linear mixed effect model (Y ~ week)

fit_pbo_est = lmer(y ~ tt + I(tt^2)  + (tt + I(tt^2)|subj),
                   data = dat_pbo_est, REML = FALSE)
fit_drg_est = lmer(y ~ tt + I(tt^2)  + (tt + I(tt^2)|subj),
                   data = dat_drg_est, REML = FALSE)

Then fit the parabolas by \[Y = e_1 + e_2 t + e_3 t^2\] where \(e = [e_1, e_2, e_3] \in \text{coef(fit_pbo_est), coef(fit_drg_est)}\)

Draw the trajectory (drg, pbo)

  • The subjects whose estimation of assignment is “placebo” by applying change score method
  • The subjects whose estimation of assignment is “drug” by applying change score method

i,e, * \(\hat n_{pbo}\): lables sets of subjects who is estimated to be assigned into placebo group * \(\hat n_{drg}\): lables sets of subjects who is estimated to be assigned into drug group

The red trajectories are drawn by \[Y = e_1 + e_2 t + e_3 t^2\] where \(e = [e_1, e_2, e_3] \in \{ \text{coef(fit_pbo_est), coef(fit_drg_est)} ; \text{coef(fit_pbo_est)}_i \in \hat n_{pbo}, \text{coef(fit_drg_est)} \in \hat n_{pbo}\}\)

The blue trajectories are drawn by \[Y = e_1 + e_2 t + e_3 t^2\] where \(e = [e_1, e_2, e_3] \in \{ \text{coef(fit_pbo_est), coef(fit_drg_est)} ; \text{coef(fit_pbo_est)}_i \in \hat n_{drg}, \text{coef(fit_drg_est)} \in \hat n_{drg}\}\)
